description: The song Summertime was written by George Gershwin, Ira Gershwin, DuBose Heyward and was first performed by Abbie Mitchell in 1935. It was first recorded and released by Helen Jepson in 1935. It was covered by Ella Fitzgerald & Louis Armstrong, Sam Cooke & Bumps Blackwell Orchestra, Peter Gabriel and 315 others.
